##ALPHA VERSION## 22.02.2014

-What you can do with this version-
->Create containers
->Start/Stop/Delete/Restart containers

-->More to come

-Requirements- (with Ubuntu 12.04)

apt-get install apache2 (libssh2 won't work with apache2.4)
apt-get install php5
apt-get install libssh2-1-dev libssh2-php 
Install docker -> http://docs.docker.io/en/latest/installation/ubuntulinux/
create user for docker + add user to docker group (make sure your user has access to docker command + ssh)
modify models/settingModel.php with the proper config file path.

-When the website is up and running
--> Create new config file with ssh credentials (in Settings menu)
--> Create at least one image on your docker server. for example : docker pull triangle/ubuntu-saucy (you can search images using docker search or create your own using a dockerfile)

